&lt;p&gt;We are currently recruiting for enthusiastic and dynamic full and part-time Health Visitors to work in the Bicester-Kidlington locality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will work as part of a well-established, supportive, corporate skill mix team delivering a high-quality professional service to clients. Bicester-Kidlington Locality has a mixed, expanding and diverse population providing excellent Health Visiting experience where you will find every day is different.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oxford Health Foundation trust provides excellent training, preceptorship and supervision for staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for motivated, innovative Band 6 Health Visitors who can rise to a challenge, demonstrating excellent communication and leadership skills. Applicants should be willing and able to lead a skill mix team, and have a thorough understanding of their Health Visiting role particularly in relation to safe guarding. Informal visits are encouraged and welcome.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Fiona Henderson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Locality Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: fiona.henderson@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07810657578&lt;/p&gt;
